text.section:
The Department shall:
provide the guidance and means for establishing child care centers for the children of State employees in State-occupied buildings or nearby buildings in accordance with this Part VIII of this subtitle;
provide for licensing of child care centers for children of State employees;
ensure that space designated within a State-occupied building or nearby buildings for a child care center complies with the prevailing local and State safety building codes for child care centers;
apply the regulations adopted under Part VII for child care centers; and
contract for child care services in the space provided. Contract providers must provide proof of financial responsibility.
